<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="273" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1452,158,1228]" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,662,688]" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Etymology</emphasis>
:—This species is named for the Serranía of Perijá, at the northern border between 
<collectingCountry box="[1290,1400,662,688]" name="Colombia" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[136,254,698,724]" name="Venezuela" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, where the species is endemic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="273" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1452,158,1228]" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,481,734,760]" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:—Only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[766,814,735,761]" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">type</typeStatus>
specimen in the peak Cerro Pintado (also spelled “Cerro del Pintao” and known as “Cerro Viruela” in 
<collectingCountry box="[642,762,770,797]" name="Venezuela" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
), which is one of the highest mountains of the Perijá serrania, reaching 
<quantity box="[241,327,806,833]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" unit="m" value="3300.0">3300 m</quantity>
(Rangel 2009). Vegetation there is sub-paramo dominated by 
<taxonomicName box="[1035,1238,806,833]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Calamagrostis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1035,1233,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Calamagrostis sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicName>
, and accompanied by several species of 
<taxonomicName box="[391,517,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
, as well as 
<emphasis box="[660,954,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">
<taxonomicName box="[660,950,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Hesperomeles" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferruginea">Hesperomeles ferruginea</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[966,1142,842,869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Otholobium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[966,1136,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Otholobium sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1161,1271,842,869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[1295,1451,843,869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Geraniaceae" genus="Geranium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1295,1444,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Geranium sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[144,286,878,905]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Geraniaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Geraniaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[350,491,879,905]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Monnina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[350,484,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Monnina sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[507,658,878,905]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Polygalaceae</taxonomicName>
) (pers. obs.). The peak is formed of upper Cretaceous limestone from the Cogollo formation, and has geomorphological evidence of glaciations (
<bibRefCitation author="Lazala, M." box="[974,1117,914,940]" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" pagination="43 - 61" refId="ref14426" refString="Lazala, M. (2007) Geologia. In: Rangel-CH, O. (Ed.) Colombia diversidad biotica V. la alta montana de la serrania de Perija. Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Bogota D. C., pp. 43 - 61." type="book chapter" year="2007">Lazala 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rodriguez, L. M. &amp; Galan, C." box="[1128,1415,914,940]" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" pagination="7 - 19" refId="ref14854" refString="Rodriguez, L. M. &amp; Galan, C. (2008) Las zonas karsticas de la Serrania de Perija, Venezuela: cavidades estudiadas y rasgos geologicoestrucurales. Boletin de la Sociedad Venezolana de Espeleologia 42: 7 - 19." type="journal article" year="2008">Rodriguez &amp; Galán 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1452,158,1228]" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,470,950,976]" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Conservation status:―</emphasis>
We included this species in the category of Critically Endangered (CR B2a,b(iii)) according to the IUCN criteria B2, because its AOO is less than 
<quantity box="[874,946,986,1012]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[946,954,986,1000]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">2</superScript>
, being only about 
<quantity box="[1169,1227,986,1012]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" unit="km" value="1.0">1 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1227,1235,986,1000]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">2</superScript>
, based on the only known population, and the EOO is less than 
<quantity box="[668,757,1022,1048]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" unit="km" value="100.0">100 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[757,765,1022,1036]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">2</superScript>
. It is found at only one location, and there is evidence of destruction of the vegetation during the last 30 years, even though this zone is included in a forest reserve (
<bibRefCitation author="Vasquez, V. H. &amp; Serrano, M. A." pageId="15" pageNumber="273" refId="ref15091" refString="Vasquez, V. H. &amp; Serrano, M. A. (2009) Las areas protegidas de Colombia. Conservacion Internacional-Colombia &amp; Fundacion Biocolombia, Bogota, 969 pp." type="book" year="2009">Vásquez &amp; Serrano 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1452,158,1228]" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,256,1130,1156]" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jara-Muñoz &amp; Richardson &amp; Zabala-Rivera" authorityYear="2021" box="[292,519,1131,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perijaensis">
<emphasis box="[292,519,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">Begonia perijaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows very close to 
<emphasis box="[770,953,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">
<taxonomicName box="[770,948,1131,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ursina">Begonia ursina</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which is the most common species of the section in the Serranía de Perijá, ranging between 2300 and 
<quantity box="[801,887,1166,1193]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" unit="m" value="3100.0">3100 m</quantity>
, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jara-Muñoz &amp; Richardson &amp; Zabala-Rivera" authorityYear="2021" box="[967,1120,1167,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="15" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perijaensis">
<emphasis box="[967,1120,1167,1192]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="273">B. perijaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the higher part of the Cerro Pintado peak.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
